related_items.title: [Maps of the former Yugoslavia relating to the Yugoslav War of 1991-1995] /
description: Relief shown by shading and spot heights on some maps. Common title devised by cataloger. Map scales range from ca. 1:4,800,000 (entire former Yugoslavia) to ca. 1:80,000 (Sarajevo vicinity). Publication date in lower margin of all maps: 8-01. Some maps include notes, graph, elevation profile, and/or index of operational groups. Some maps include none of these. Production numbers in lower margin range from "753541AI (A04646)" to "753556AI (R00389)". Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image.
